    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Grid</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Use grid to position content, control layout behavior, and create consistent responsive page structures across endpoint management workflows.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

          <!-- Intro -->
          <div class="doc-section" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--prism-text-muted); max-width: 760px;">In Prism, grid is the structural foundation behind dashboards, device inventory, patching, policy builders, alert triage, compliance reporting, and remediation experiences.</p>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--prism-text-muted); max-width: 760px; margin-top: 12px;">A strong grid system improves scan speed, layout consistency, and engineering predictability across complex enterprise screens.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Grid anatomy -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="grid-anatomy" class="doc-section-title">Grid anatomy</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Prism grid has three core elements.</p>

            <h3 id="columns" class="doc-h3">Columns</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Columns divide the page into equal vertical sections and organize content zones. Use columns for:</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Dashboard cards</li>
              <li>Table containers</li>
              <li>Form layouts</li>
              <li>Drawer content regions</li>
              <li>Wizard steps</li>
              <li>Analytics widgets</li>
            </ul>

            <!-- Visual diagram -->
            <div style="padding: 32px; border: 2px dashed var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 20px; position: relative;">
              <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-end; gap: 0; position: relative;">
                <div style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); writing-mode: vertical-rl; transform: rotate(180deg); margin-right: 12px; font-weight: 600;">Margin</div>
                <div style="flex: 1; display: flex; gap: 4px;">
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                  <div style="flex: 1; height: 80px; background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.10); border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15); border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                </div>
                <div style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); writing-mode: vertical-rl; margin-left: 12px; font-weight: 600;">Margin</div>
              </div>
              <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-weight: 600;">Gutter between each column</div>
            </div>

            <h3 id="gutters" class="doc-h3" style="margin-top: 32px;">Gutters</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Gutters are the spaces between columns. They separate content consistently and prevent dense enterprise pages from visually collapsing.</p>

            <h3 id="margins" class="doc-h3" style="margin-top: 32px;">Margins</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Margins define the outer layout boundary. They ensure content never touches viewport edges, especially on:</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Large monitoring screens</li>
              <li>Compact laptops</li>
              <li>Zoomed accessibility states</li>
              <li>Responsive tablet views</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Grid types -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="grid-types" class="doc-section-title">Grid types</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Prism supports two grid types based on task density.</p>

            <h3 id="fluid-grid" class="doc-h3"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">1.</span> Fluid grid</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Fluid grids stretch to fill the available main content area.</p>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 20px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
              <div style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--prism-text); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 12px;">Best for</div>
              <ul class="doc-list">
                <li>Device inventory</li>
                <li>Threat dashboards</li>
                <li>Patch status boards</li>
                <li>Alert queues</li>
                <li>Analytics views</li>
                <li>Heatmaps</li>
                <li>Compliance matrices</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.12); border-radius: 12px;">
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Rule:</strong> Use fluid grid whenever table width, widget count, or live telemetry density is high.</p>
            </div>

            <h3 id="fixed-grid" class="doc-h3" style="margin-top: 32px;"><span style="color: var(--prism-violet); font-weight: 700; margin-right: 4px;">2.</span> Fixed grid</h3>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Fixed grids apply a controlled maximum width. Prism supports <code>fixed.narrow</code> and <code>fixed.wide</code>.</p>

            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
                <h4 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 12px;">Fixed narrow</h4>
                <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Use for readability-first workflows:</p>
                <ul class="doc-list">
                  <li>Policy creation</li>
                  <li>Step forms</li>
                  <li>AI remediation summaries</li>
                  <li>Guided troubleshooting</li>
                  <li>Documentation panels</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
                <h4 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 12px;">Fixed wide</h4>
                <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;">Use for balanced dense pages:</p>
                <ul class="doc-list">
                  <li>Software repository</li>
                  <li>Deployment workflows</li>
                  <li>Audit reports</li>
                  <li>Security investigation pages</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.12); border-radius: 12px;">
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">Avoid fixed layouts for real-time dense dashboards.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Breakpoints -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="breakpoints" class="doc-section-title">Breakpoints</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Prism follows a 6-breakpoint responsive grid system aligned to enterprise viewport realities.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead>
                <tr><th>Breakpoint</th><th>Viewport</th><th>Columns</th><th>Gutters</th><th>Margins</th></tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>xxs</code></td><td>320&ndash;479px</td><td>2</td><td>12px</td><td>16px</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>xs</code></td><td>480&ndash;767px</td><td>6</td><td>12px</td><td>16px</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>s</code></td><td>768&ndash;1023px</td><td>6</td><td>12px</td><td>16px</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>m</code></td><td>1024&ndash;1439px</td><td>12</td><td>16px</td><td>32px</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>l</code></td><td>1440&ndash;1767px</td><td>12</td><td>16px</td><td>32px</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>xl</code></td><td>1768px+</td><td>12</td><td>16px</td><td>32px</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Column span rules -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="column-spans" class="doc-section-title">Column span rules</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Prism uses a 12-column layout for desktop enterprise workflows.</p>

            <h3 id="recommended-spans" class="doc-h3">Recommended spans</h3>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead>
                <tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Span</th></tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Full-width tables</td><td>12</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Two equal panels</td><td>6 / 6</td></tr>
                <tr><td>KPI dashboard cards</td><td>3 / 3 / 3 / 3</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Primary + inspector</td><td>8 / 4</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Policy form + live preview</td><td>7 / 5</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Chart + insights</td><td>8 / 4</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>

            <!-- Visual demo -->
            <div class="grid-demo-container" style="margin-top: 24px;">
              <div style="font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 16px;">Layout patterns</div>
              <div class="grid-demo-row">
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 12;">12</div>
              </div>
              <div class="grid-demo-row">
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 8;">8</div>
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 4;">4</div>
              </div>
              <div class="grid-demo-row">
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 7;">7</div>
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 5;">5</div>
              </div>
              <div class="grid-demo-row">
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 6;">6</div>
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 6;">6</div>
              </div>
              <div class="grid-demo-row">
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 3;">3</div>
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 3;">3</div>
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 3;">3</div>
                <div class="grid-col" style="flex: 3;">3</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.12); border-radius: 12px;">
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Rule:</strong> Content should span at least 3 columns for readability and structure. Avoid 1-column desktop content blocks except for status rails, timeline markers, and utility action strips.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Column offset -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="column-offset" class="doc-section-title">Column offset</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Not every layout must consume all 12 columns. Use offsets to:</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Center onboarding empty states</li>
              <li>Focus critical warnings</li>
              <li>Narrow AI-generated summaries</li>
              <li>Present single-task confirmation flows</li>
              <li>Reduce cognitive load in destructive workflows</li>
            </ul>
            <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 20px 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
              <div style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Example</div>
              <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">A policy review screen may span 8 columns with 2-column offsets on each side.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider" />

          <!-- Endpoint-specific grid patterns -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="endpoint-patterns" class="doc-section-title">Endpoint-specific grid patterns</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px;">
              <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px;">
                <h4 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 12px;">Device inventory</h4>
                <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); line-height: 1.8;">
